<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-45-0293 </DOCNO><TEXT>This article reports on the automation of a furnace and materials handlingproduction line designed for the hardening and heat treatment of harrowdiscs made of steel. The implementation of the line and its automationis described for a specific Soviet plant. Data are cited on enhancedproductivity, utilization of power, quality control, and process controlwhich can be attributed directly to automation measures and equipment.Electrical power savings were found to amount to 426,000 kilowatt-hoursannually.</TEXT></DOC>